# Go Formatting

After creating or editing any Go file, run `gofmt` on every changed file before finishing the task. CI linters will reject unformatted code.

## Required workflow

1. Make the Go code change.
2. Format all changed `.go` files:

```bash
gofmt -w path/to/changed/file.go
```

For multiple files:

```bash
gofmt -w path/to/file1.go path/to/file2.go
```

3. Verify formatting was applied (re-read the file or run `gofmt -l` and confirm no output).

## Notes

- `gofmt -w` is preferred over `go fmt ./...` when only specific files changed — it is explicit and avoids formatting unrelated packages.
- `go fmt` and `gofmt` produce the same output; either is acceptable as long as every changed file is formatted.
- Go code lives under `go/` in a workspace (`go/go.work`). Run commands from the containing module directory when needed.
